author: jtaylor
msg: - Refactoring the memory caches, based on some of the things we've been
discussing and some of the comments. MemoryCache no longer extends any
other interfaces (ICache or ICacheType) since all the methods implemented
from those were not needed. I also tried to simplify any existing methods
where possible. The idea here is that the MemoryCache is not a general
purpose cache, rather it is a component of a cache region managed by
a 'Cache'. I also pushed up and renamed IMemoryCache. I think this
- Moving some constants out of ICache. Need to go further -- there are
places here where a typesafe enum would be more appropriate.
